  "prompt": "What percentage of the world population is religious?",
  "response": "Estimating the percentage of the world population that is religious can be challenging due to variations in data sources, definitions of religiosity, and changes over time. However, as of recent estimates, about 84% to 85% of the global population is affiliated with a religion. This includes adherents of major world religions such as Christianity, Islam, Hinduism, Buddhism, and others, in addition to people who identify with indigenous or folk religions.\n\nIt's important to note that levels of religiosity can vary significantly within countries and regions, and some people who identify with a religion may not actively practice it, while others may be spiritual but not affiliated with any organized religion.",
